    <h4>Basic HTML Tags</h4>
    <p>HTML uses tags like <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;a&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;p&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;img&gt;</code>, etc.</p>
    <p>Some tags (like <code>&lt;br&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;hr&gt;</code>) don’t need closing tags. They are called empty tags.</p>

    <h4>Features of HTML</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Easy to learn</li>
        <li>Works on all browsers</li>
        <li>Platform-independent</li>
        <li>Supports multimedia (images, audio, video)</li>
        <li>Allows linking between pages</li>
        <li>Can be integrated with other languages</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Why Learn HTML?</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Works on all browsers</li>
        <li>Completely free</li>
        <li>Easy to learn</li>
        <li>Foundation for other languages</li>
        <li>Essential for web developers</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Advantages of HTML</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Free to use</li>
        <li>Fast and lightweight</li>
        <li>Browser friendly</li>
        <li>Easy to learn</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Disadvantages of HTML</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Can only create static pages</li>
        <li>Large code for complex pages</li>
        <li>Weak security</li>
        <li>Not suitable for dynamic tasks alone</li>
    </ul>
